info.description:
Escape to the desert with our charming bungalow in Terlingua, Texas. This bohemian retreat is the perfect getaway for those looking for privacy and tranquility. The bungalow boasts unique boho design touches, making it a cozy and stylish space to relax in after a day of exploring the beautiful Big Bend National Park, just a short drive away. Whether you're looking to hike, stargaze or simply unwind, this desert oasis is the perfect place to make unforgettable memories.
**The space**
This bungalow boasts a minimalistic boho design, with small but unique decor touches that create a warm and inviting atmosphere. The highlight of the interior is the large 5-window front facing the beautiful desert sunset, providing an incredible natural light and an amazing view of the sunset that can be enjoyed throughout the bungalow. Not only does it offer full privacy in the middle of the desert, but it also features an outdoor space that includes a relaxing hammock, where you can enjoy the beautiful views and the peaceful desert ambiance.
Our bungalow offers a solar shower and a solar panel that works during daylight, and a solar light that works at night. However, please be aware that we do not have running water or electricity. We provide a small sink and a solar shower, but please bring your own water to fill them up. 
You will have your own private bathroom and will be able to use a composting toilet. Please make sure to be familiar with the instructions prior to using it.
Please check the weather before you arrive and it might be a good idea to bring an additional blanket if it gets cold. If you are traveling with more people, feel free to check our other bungalows, they are located on the same property about 100 yards away. 
So, come and experience the serenity of the desert while staying in our cozy bungalow, and make memories that will last a lifetime!
**Guest access**
Nestled within our picturesque 5-acre property, located 64 miles south of Alpine along Highway 118, lies our charming bungalow. Only a 25-minute drive from the historic Terlingua Ghost Town and half an hour from the entrance of the renowned Big Bend National Park, our off-grid bungalow is easily accessible via well-maintained roads, suitable for any type of vehicle. We invite you to explore the beauty of our property, but kindly request that you respect and refrain from disturbing the local wildlife. Thank you!
**Other things to note**
To avoid any misunderstandings:
We provide:

- Toilet 
- Solar shower
- Bed & Bedding
- Sink 
 
Please bring:
- water for sink and shower
- Toilet paper (just in the unlikely case weâ€˜re out of stock)
- Towels
- Sheets
Note: we run on a self cleaning policy, where every guest has to clean up when they check out. Please keep that in mind when you book. :)

info.description:
Prepare to be blown away by the exquisite architecture and views that just don't stop.  WE GUARANTEE THIS WILL BE THE MOST AMAZING AIRBNB EVER!  This modern mountain home was just remodeled and sits on over 2 acres. It is nestled in an aspen forest making it the perfect place to get away from it all, yet it is less than 5 miles from the heart of Telluride and only 3 miles to the free Mountain Village parking garage with ski-in/ski-out access and a free gondola that drops you right into Telluride
**The space**
When architect Jack Young designed this home he had a clear goal to bring the outside in. With the 20' walls of floor-to-ceiling windows, it feels like you are in a treehouse. The towering walls of glass allow you to fully appreciate the surrounding aspen forest and killer views of the iconic Wilson's Peaks. These famous mountains are the same mountains pictured in the Coors Light logo.
This 2700 sq ft home has  2 private bedrooms and 2 baths with a â€œ3rd bedroomâ€ that is a loft area located in the master bedroom. The flexible sleeping options provide space for up to 8 people including children.  However, with the layout, we recommend no more than four to six adults to maximize your comfort.       
The updated kitchen features high end appliances such as a 36â€ Wolf cooktop, and Liebherr built-in fridge. It is fully stocked with all the pots, pans, and cooking utensils needed to cook a gourmet meal. We provide a drip coffee maker with Starbucks coffee beans, basic spices and cooking oil. 
The master suite has a private entrance and hot tub access, an ensuite bathroom, a jacuzzi bathtub, a king bed, a desk, and a loft space with a second king bed.  This loft space is considered "Bedroom 3," so the Master bedroom and loft combined can sleep 4. 
The second bedroom also has a king bed with a sitting area and spa-inspired bathroom with a steam shower across the hall.
There are two daybeds in the main hallway that convert into twin beds to sleep two additional people.
We have recently installed A/C which is rare in Telluride, but is a huge plus on hot summer afternoons.  In the winter, there is not a more cozy place to stay. With in-floor heating in the living room and bathroom, two gas furnaces with whole house humidifiers, wood stove and tons of solar gain from the windows you will be cozy even when the temp drops below zero.
There is a Sonos music system throughout the house that is also tied into the high fidelity 2-channel electrostatic speaker system in the living room.  There is over $10,000 worth of audio/video equipment in our house, so your ears will be happy!
Outside there is a brand new 6 person hot tub and a new a Webber propane grill.
**Guest access**
Our guests have full access to our entire two acre property as well as the surrounding nature preserve and neighborhood hiking trails.
**Other things to note**
There are no blinds on any of the windows. However, being on two acres surrounded by a dense aspen forest the house is still very private. 
There is another small house on the property that shares a driveway and parking area, but it is positioned so that there is still complete privacy. There are NO shared common outdoor spaces between the two houses. 
There are only two private bedrooms, the â€œ3rd bedroomâ€ is located in the loft of the Master suite.  This loft requires climbing a ladder to access and has low ceilings, so it is generally recommended for older kids and teens, but may not be comfortable for adults and may not be safe for young kids.
We provide a enough disposable items for a typical weekend stay, if you are staying longer or think you may need more of these items, please bring extra for your trip. Here is what we provide : 1 bag of ground Starbucks coffee for our drip coffee maker, coffee filters, 2 rolls of paper towels, 3 rolls of toilet paper per bathroom, salt/pepper, cooking oil, cleaning spray, dish soap, laundry detergent for 2-3 loads, full sized bottles of shampoo, conditioner, and body wash, and a bundle of firewood for 1-2 fires. Additional firewood can be purchased from the gas station 3 miles away.

info.description:
Welcome to the TreeLoft experience! This is a custom built luxury treehouse for two.  It is our hope that upon your stay you will be reconnected to nature and to the one you came with.  We created the TreeLoft with an inspired state of mind, and we are hopeful that same inspiration will be experienced and reflected during your stay.  Go to sleep counting stars and wake up with the trees!  We can't wait to provide you with the TreeLoft experience! We rise by lifting others!
**The space**
Privately and intentionally nestled into the woods of our 120 acre farm you'll find our elevated TreeLoft amongst the astonishing trees of Missouri.  With all our friends in mind, entry is effortless with our ramp walkway with plenty of space for wheel chair access throughout if needed. Upon entry, unfold your eyes on the natural light that pours through the expansive windows that make it known you are in the trees!  
Grab a blanket and cozy up next to the modern gas fireplace for those cool evenings. Thereâ€™s a skylight just above the king size bed for night sky gazing with a remote solar shade to keep you sleeping in the wee morning hours. A rain shower for two in the walk through bathroom including a relaxing soaking tub and plush robes for your comfort. The kitchen offers an indoor/outdoor coffee bar and tiny appliances for all your cooking needs. Outdoors you'll find a hot tub placed sweetly next to towering Eastern Red Cedar trees with a privacy fence, a separate deck for grilling or nesting in the trees and fire-pit below with ambient lighting for smores or story telling!
There is very limited cellphone service, no wifi or television at the TreeLoft with intention to truly allow our guests the authentic experience of disconnecting. We strive to provide you with all that you might need to make you feel like you donâ€™t need to leave the TreeLoft for a day trip (however we totally support an outing or two as well). There are games to play, books and magazines to get lost in and even a few puzzles if thatâ€™s your thing. Be sure to download your favorite playlist before you arrive so that you can use our bluetooth speaker to take with you to the hot tub or coffee deck. Dance! Laugh or heck, cry if you need to. Just BE in the trees and BE with the one you came with, even if you come by yourself. Slow down, breath deep, nurture and hopefully, just maybe, youâ€™ll leave more awake to the life you must step back into.
Thank you for choosing the TreeLoft for your stay!
**Guest access**
The TreeLoft is on our family farm, in which we call BaseCamp at CedarFork. It is indeed one of our favorite places to take our family and enjoy the slower sweet moments of life.  You may hear us drive through in our vehicle or utv, however we will always keep your privacy in mind and stay a good distance away from the TreeLoft. By all means if you would like to visit us, we are always open to meet our guests!
**Other things to note**
We now have a bunker storm shelter within 150 feet of the TreeLoft for the safety of all our guests! With the lack of service and Missouriâ€™s unpredictable weather, we do still ask that you monitor the forecast prior to your stay so that you are aware of times you may need to watch for severe weather. Being prepared can make your trip so much more enjoyable.

info.description:
You will feel the stresses of life wash away as you sway in the trees and listen to the sounds of the beautiful stream just feet from the treehouse deck.  You'll never want to leave!  Enjoy a bit of solitude or some special alone time with a loved one.  It's hard to beat Stone City Treehouse to make your time away special!
**The space**
After your day of hiking, skiing, or touring local breweries and distilleries, come home to this beautiful, private tiny house in the trees!  Or, just spend the day lazily relaxing by the fire and reading, while the sound of the stream soothes you.
Walk through the woods, up the stairs, and enter into another dimension - one that you won't want to leave!  Much thought was put into the design and local, natural, and recycled materials were a priority in its construction.
Soak in the curated interior design while you relax in the living room space and gaze out the large, recycled windows (from an old, local schoolhouse). 
Enjoy the deck that overlooks the year-round stream (that may be frozen over in the winter) and let the sound of the water wash through you.  You may even see some critters if you're still enough!
There is a sweet sitting area, hammock, and campfire space just below the treehouse right on the stream, with a dramatic view of the treehouse.  And a hanging bed underneath!
You can cook simple meals on the propane campstove (with a griddle option) or use the small charcoal grill in the space under the treehouse.  There is a mini-fridge with a separate freezer to keep your fresh produce from the farmers' market and your yummy local beer nice and cool.  There's a very primitive (and limited) water system you can use for washing dishes.
We also provide some basic condiments and cooking basics, like olive oil and salt and pepper.  We also offer coffee, hot chocolate, and lemonade.  Most of the products we offer for your use, and our cleaning supplies and paper products are from Public Goods and you can get a 25% discount on your first purchase with the coupon code TREEHOUSEPGA
There is a basic composting toilet in the treehouse for your convenience, but you also have access to a full, modern bathroom at the house, with a beautiful shower.
When it's time for bed, climb up the loft ladder to "The Nest" and sink into the  comfy bed. Open up the windows to hear the nighttime sounds of the stream and the forest!
We prioritize our earth and take environmental considerations into every decision: we generate solar electricity; we compost and recycle; we use environmentally friendly cleaning products; we avoid disposable items as much as possible; and we used many local and recycled materials in the construction of the treehouse.
The interior structure is 10'x16' with a loft and the deck is 4'x16'.
**Guest access**
You have exclusive access to the entire treehouse.
The treehouse is about 200 feet from the driveway and house, yet it's very private in the woods.  
I have a garden cart you can use to transport your belongings to the treehouse.  
If you arrive early and the treehouse is not ready yet, you are welcome to leave your things on the porch at the house.
**Other things to note**
You must be physically able to climb stairs and ladders to stay here.   The sleeping space is in a somewhat-tight loft, but the limited space has not been an issue for even our taller guests.  We do not allow dogs (or any other pets) in the sleeping loft.
This area of Vermont (the Northeast Kingdom) has snow all winter, and sometimes mud, especially in the spring.  The treehouse is located on a dirt/gravel road that can sometimes be challenging if it's muddy or even snowy or icy.  We can get a lot of snow sometimes and you could possibly get stuck on your way here or in the driveway.  I do my best to keep the driveway clean and sanded, but it's not always possible all of the time.  We live in a rural area and services are not always immediately available.  
All of that being said, most of the time there are no issues but if you have access to a 4WD vehicle, ideally with higher clearance and snow tires, that is the best-case scenario.  Keep an eye on the weather and plan ahead: the Northeast Kingdom of Vermont is probably not like where you're from and being prepared for the weather and challenging driving conditions is absolutely the best policy.
There is a primitive compost toilet in the treehouse, with regular bathroom access (toilet, sink, washer, dryer, shower) in the main house, which is about 200 feet away.  
Wifi is not (barely?) available at the treehouse, but it is at the house.  There is a phone (landline) at the treehouse and minimal/intermittent cell reception.
I provide at least two gallons of water that can be used for either drinking and/or washing.  I encourage you to fill the water up at the house if you need more than this (there is a faucet option in the shower) rather than bringing in bottles.  Our water is great!  
There is a camping cookstove available (with a griddle), a charcoal grill, toaster oven, and a mini-fridge.  You should be able to find all you need for basic cooking there.
Please understand that you are likely to come across various critters - anything from fairly large spiders (most likely - they love the water) to bears and moose (less likely).  Walking down to the treehouse you may come across our resident chipmunk, and will often hear owls and loons at night.  So, if you want to stay here you must be comfortable with insects and wildlife!  We are in the woods and nature and spiders and insects are part of the package.
info.title: Lovely Treehouse in the Woods next to Stream

Welcome to the EcoFriendly A-Frame in Hildale, Utah. This extraordinary 144 sq ft, solar powered A-frame cabin is conveniently located 50 min from Zion NP & 2 hours from Bryce Canyon NP. 
Its unique feature window wall opens up to bring in the stunning views of the south side of the Zion Mountains. In addition to the private bathroom located next to the cabin, guests will have their own observation deck, grilling station & fire pit. So grab a travel buddy & come explore Southern Utah!
**The space**
ðŸŽðŸ” FREE ATV TOUR for all of our MAY GUESTS: To kick off Spring, we are offering a free 20-minute ATV ride through our favorite ATV trails in town to all of our guests! As locals from the area, we wanted a fun, unique way to get to know our guests and show off some of our favorite canyon viewpoints- the perfect way to explore the Canaan Mountain Range like a local! More info can be found in the "Other Things to Note" section. ðŸŽðŸ”
Our 12ft x 12ft A-frame has one large studio space with a king-sized bed. The solar-powered cabin has overhead lighting & outlets for charging. The private, full sized bathroom is located in a separate building next to the cabin. One side of the cabin has a convertible window wall that can open and extend out to your private observation deck, an amazing way to soak in the red-canyon views! The deck doubles as dining and cooking areas with a table for two, a barbecue grill, and a sun umbrella. Just a few steps from the deck and cabin is a firepit that guests can use to provide warmth when it becomes too chilly for comfort. Just behind the cabin is the restroom.
Studio Space:
- King sized bed
- Bedding linens
Observation Deck:
The observation deck speaks for itself, overlooking the south Zion mountain range in all its glory. The breathtaking view of our local El Capitan mountains is our guest's favorite part about their stay in our eco-friendly cabin. The deck is equipped with a dining and cooking area with a table for two and a barbecue grill, with the following offerings: 
- Propane Grill (propane provided)
- Insulated cooler
- Salt, Pepper, Olive Oil, Aluminum Foil
- Grill tongs, grill brush, grill spatula, 1 small pot, 1 small pan
- Eating Utensils for 2: plates, cups, bowls, silverware, steak knives, wine cups
- Misc.: French Press, wine/cap opener, 1 cutting knife, 1 cutting board
- Fire-pit w/ 1 bundle of firewood.
The Bathroom:
The bathroom has a fully functioning toilet & shower and a propane heated shower. We stock the bathroom with: 
- 2 Bath Towels
- 1 Hand Towel
- Shampoo
- Conditioner
- Body Wash
- Handsoap
Since it is located in a separate building next to the cabin, we recommend packing slippers/a bathroom caddy to make it easy to go back and forth. 
Fire Pit:
Just a few steps from the deck and cabin is a firepit for guests to share smores under the stars. Note, we provide one stack of firewood. Firewood for purchase is located at Bee's Marketplace,  7 minutes away. Gathering of firewood on site is prohibited. 
Note: there are 4 other cabins spaced apart on this property. They're spaced strategically to give you ample privacy, about 10-15 yards apart from each other amongst the trees. Please see the aerial photo in the listing to get a view of the full site.
**Guest access**
ðŸœ The EcoFriendly A-Frame is located on a 2 acre cabin site with 5 units total. Each unit has a private bathroom, deck, fire pit, etc. There are no shared spaces. 
ðŸœ There is a rural neighborhood to the west of the cabin and undisturbed public lands - ideal for walking and exploration - to the north. Southern Utah has some of the most renowned ATV riding trails in the country, leaving guests with the possibility to hear ATV's from time to time.
ðŸœ The land surrounding the canyons is BLM land and open for public use. Feel free to hike directly from our site into the surrounding canyons.
**Other things to note**
ðŸŽðŸ” FREE ATV TOUR for all of our MAY GUESTS: To kick off Spring, we are offering a free 20-minute ATV ride through our favorite ATV trails in town to all of our guests! As locals from the area, we wanted a fun, unique way to get to know our guests and show off some of our favorite canyon viewpoints- the perfect way to explore the Canaan Mountain Range like a local! If you are interested in a free ATV ride with Lee, the property owner, please let us know at least 24 hours before the day of check-in. Give us a couple of time options that work for you and we will confirm a time. Lee will pick you up from the cabin and take you on a 20-minute tour through Hildale, Utah to a couple of canyon lookouts and ATV trails. Reservations for the tour can be made at the time of booking up to 24 hours before check-in. ðŸŽðŸ” 
Check-In: 3PM MST, Check Out: 10AM MST
While you have the luxury of a personal bathroom and king size bed, please note you are in the high desert and that this experience is still similar to camping. You may experience high winds. In the summer there can be very high temperature weather and in the winter there can be very low temperatures, please pack accordingly as this will have a large impact on your stay. There will be sand, bugs, squirrels, and possibly snakes that you may encounter. While this is not common, it is still a possibility.
Food Storage: insulated cooler.
Pet Policy: 
Pets are happily allowed at the Angels Landing A-Frame for a flat $25 fee, to be paid at time of booking. If you plan to bring a pet, there are a few rules that must be followed:

2. Pets are not allowed on the furniture, specifically the bed. By booking this cabin, you are agreeing to pay a $25 pet fee. 
3. Please clean up after your pet. If excessive damage is incurred during your stay, we will charge you for additional cleaning/repair fees. 
If you are planning on streaming videos, we recommend bringing a hotspot. Cell phone service is reliable however we do not provide Wifi. Free wifi is available at the coffee shop and lounge area on the 2nd floor of Bee's Marketplace, making it a great place to get work done if needed.

info.description:
Meticulously designer-renovated cabin surrounded by mature evergreens and nestled behind a charming seasonal creek. Whether youâ€™re looking to spend time with loved ones or work remotely outside of the city, this is the place to do it all. Relax by the fireplace while light pours in from the wall of windows, grill and chill on the deck, and explore nature right outside your front door. Conveniently located near everything Lake Arrowhead has to offer. You'll never want to leave!
**The space**
Upstairs, a spacious lofted bedroom with vaulted ceilings has the best views in the cabin - imagine seeing nothing but trees when you open your eyes. The main level has two more bedrooms with a luxuriously-sized king in one and two smaller beds in the other - perfect for kids or friends that each want their own place to sleep! Full ensuite bathroom in the loft and another full bathroom on the main level with a tub. 
The gorgeous kitchen has brand new designer appliances and everything else you need to cook a fabulous meal or just make a perfect cup of coffee in the morning. Sliding doors open onto a deck outfitted with a Weber gas grill, a firepit and seating for birdwatching and stargazing. The large flat lot features a seasonal creek and a picnic table surrounded by towering trees - perfect for eating that gourmet home cooked meal you just whipped up (or takeout from one of the awesome restaurants nearby). 
This cabin has all the elements needed for a peaceful retreat surrounded by nature without skimping on any of the modern amenities we all love, including fast WiFi, a flatscreen TV, and central heat and A/C (a rare find in Lake Arrowhead cabins!).

info.description:
The perfect place for to wake up in the trees or spend a weekend with friends!
 Relax in tranquility and scenic beauty from your own porch! Surrounded by state land just minutes from numerous hiking trails and waterfalls in promised land state park.  Enjoy a dip in one of the nearby lakes or toasty fire on a cold night inside by the wood stove.
**The space**
The house is situated in a small wooded community 10mins from promised land state park with public access to hiking trails, docks, a beach, fishing, canoe and kayak rentals, and waterfalls. It's only a 25 min drive from Lake Wallenpaupack, and close to numerous quaint little towns, state forests, antique stores, local markets, and 15 min from skytop for skiing and snow tubing. Inside you will find a wood burning fire place, Wi-Fi, record player with record collection, board games, fully stocked kitchen, linens and towels, comfortable beds, and modern furniture.
The space is well-suited for a couple, a small family, or up to 4 friends.
My fully-furnished 2-BR cabin is located only 90 miles from Manhattan in the Pocono lake region.  Around the area you can find skiing, hiking, tubing, waterfalls, state forests, antique stores, farm stands, and local markets. The community is packed full of soaring trees, boulders, and streams--and also cardinals, turkeys, foxes, and lots of deer who often laze around in my yard : ) A fire pit, back deck, outdoor seating and grill complete the outdoor experience.
Inside, the fire place fills the cabin with coziness and warmth. Features and amenities include ceiling fans, electric baseboard heaters in every room, High Speed Internet/Wi-Fi, 60 inch smart tv, record player with record collection, board games, fully stocked kitchen, linens and towels, beach towels,  lawn chairs, comfortable beds, and modern furniture.
The space is well-suited for a couple, a small family, or a few friends. Both the master bedroom and upstairs loft room have queen-size beds with dressers and closets to store your things.

info.description:
The â€˜Schoolhouseâ€™ is a newly constructed modern home designed around the principle of adaptive re-use, and offers you a unique architectural living space in a prime location; 10 minutes from the west entrance to Joshua Tree National Park, 2 minutes to downtown Joshua tree cafes and shopping, 15 minutes to Yucca Valley and 45 minutes to Palm Springs.
**The space**
This quiet and private property is bordered by dramatic rock outcroppings, hiking trails, and expansive views of the Mojave Desert valley on the north side.   One unique feature of this home is its floor-to-ceiling glass walls;  youâ€™ll have an unobstructed experience of the desert landscape in all its glory--star-filled skies, magnificent boulders, and wildlife galore!  Jackrabbits, quails, roadrunners, chipmunks, albino lizards, rosy boas, coyotes, and more are frequently seen in and around the property.   
Our 2 bedroom, 2 bath home can accommodate up to four adult guests and children older than 10 years!   The bedrooms and adjoining bathrooms are situated at opposite ends of the living/dining area for privacy.   Premium queen and  full-size hybrid mattresses (encased in hygienic waterproof mattress protectors) and 100% cotton sheets/bedding are provided for your sleeping comfort.    
Two outside decks, a plunge pool, and an outdoor shower allow you to enjoy indoor/outdoor desert living.
**Guest access**
Joshua Tree National Park is open year-round. There are few facilities within the park's approximately 800,000 acres, making Joshua Tree a true desert wilderness just a few hours outside Los Angeles, San Diego, Las Vegas, and Phoenix. About 2.8 million visitors come to the park each year to enjoy activities such as hiking, camping, photography, rock climbing, and simply enjoying the serene desert scenery. The busy season in Joshua Tree runs from October through May. You can enjoy activities like Camping, Hiking, Ranger Programs, Photography, Birding, Experience dark Night Skies, Biking, Rock Climbing, Backpacking, and Horse Riding! Come visit.
Guest at school house may use joshua tree park annual pass card for free as long you return it back otherwise will charge you the cost of loosing the card $80
**Other things to note**
The Schoolhouse; a synthesis of modern architecture and recycled materials, is a modern home.
The architect who embraces this philosophy, the house acquired prefabricated metal classroom structures, cement board panels, concrete drain pipes, and other materials destined for the landfill, and transformed them into an environmentally conductive, and aesthetically pleasing dwelling for your enjoyment.
**License number**
CESTRP-2021-01012
